caption: Just to mess with him put them back on the tree.
This is your first abduction, isn’t it?
Must be valuable, they spend hours collecting them!
Wait, did they say 'take the man and leave' or 'take the man and leaves?'
Trust me—I know their language. If he’s ‘raking it in,’ it’s money.
We travel 1,000 light years and you miss by three feet.
No, the OTHER pile of useless organic matter.
After the year they’ve had, it’s the least we can do.
As long as we're up here we should do the gutters.
Can’t wait to see the look on his face when we put these back on the tree.
Put them in the neighbor's yard so he has to say aliens did it."
I AM getting the intelligent life form! The other one still hasn’t accepted the election results.
I think you've slightly misinterpreted "A good interplanetary explorer discreetly gathers information and leaves."
What trouble?  We just beam them up and dump them over the fence.  I've seen him do it dozens of times.
Please let it taste better than kale.
I guess his wife is the hunter.
This advanced species makes oxygen, reduces CO2, and changes colors.
First, you get them to believe you are here to help them.
Idiot! That’s the lawn tractor beam.
I guess the trees make them do it.  Wait until you see what the dogs make them do.
Why do you only do chores on other planets?
The human next door wants us to abduct his, too.
Another American job lost to an  illegal alien.
I said hover not hoover.
He’s spent all afternoon collecting them - they must be worth SOMETHING
I find that random acts of kindness before the anal probe always helps.
The real fun starts when his wife gets home and we beam them back down again.
He was collecting them. They must be important.
Then we'll dump them in the yard down the street where they cut down all their trees.
If they only knew our money grows on their trees.
